31:40.398 --> 31:41.774
Okay, gross.

31:41.858 --> 31:44.485
I'm not discussing my sex life
in front of my brother.

31:44.569 --> 31:46.654
Not that there's anything to discuss.

31:49.532 --> 31:51.242
Sometimes, I wish I was normal.

31:51.326 --> 31:52.660
Well, dude...

31:53.286 --> 31:54.370
nobody's normal.

31:59.292 --> 32:01.252
[breathes deeply]

32:20.355 --> 32:23.358
In fourth grade,
my biology teacher, Mr. Durocher--

32:23.441 --> 32:27.403
he was fat-- said penguins are similar
to humans...

32:28.696 --> 32:32.408
because once they copulate,
they stay with the same partner for life.

32:33.159 --> 32:35.453
So, what about you? What's your life like?

32:35.536 --> 32:37.538
-Mm.
-[chuckles]

32:38.081 --> 32:41.000
Well, ironically, when I was in college,

32:41.084 --> 32:43.211
I also dated a girl for about a month.

32:43.294 --> 32:44.629
[laughs]

32:44.712 --> 32:46.506
Mm. [laughs]

32:46.589 --> 32:49.258
And I am a hairdresser.

32:49.342 --> 32:50.593
Yours is too short.

32:50.677 --> 32:51.678
[chuckles]

32:52.470 --> 32:55.014
You're funny. And kind of mean.

32:55.098 --> 32:56.933
[both chuckle]

32:57.892 --> 33:00.144
Yeah, I'm always mean to people I like.

33:00.770 --> 33:02.939
I think it's 'cause I expect so much.

33:03.815 --> 33:05.108
So you like me.

33:05.191 --> 33:06.818
[both laugh]

33:08.027 --> 33:10.071
[Sam]  But according to the 2010 census,

33:10.154 --> 33:12.365
which is the most recent data
I could acquire,

33:12.448 --> 33:15.034
49% of marriages end in divorce.

33:17.662 --> 33:19.414
Sorry. Um...

33:21.666 --> 33:23.501
You know, um...

33:23.584 --> 33:26.421
if you turn the heat up
on your dishwasher,

33:26.504 --> 33:29.882
you won't have those ugly white spots
on the glasses. Just so...

33:42.353 --> 33:43.813
[Sam]  Penguins mate for life.

33:45.648 --> 33:48.317
So penguins aren't like people.

33:53.031 --> 33:54.490
They're better.

34:15.553 --> 34:17.680
I wonder if they ever get tired
of swimming.

34:18.181 --> 34:19.307
They don't.

34:23.644 --> 34:26.981
You know, Casey...
told me what happened...

34:28.357 --> 34:29.650
with the girl.

34:31.861 --> 34:33.279
I wish I had a time machine.

34:33.362 --> 34:36.699
I would go back in time
and never ask her out

34:36.783 --> 34:39.243
and also maybe visit
the Middle Ages because...

34:39.327 --> 34:40.578
jousting.

34:41.621 --> 34:45.208
Look, I don't know about some
of that stuff you're into,

34:45.291 --> 34:48.377
but girls I know about, okay?
And they're tough.

34:49.670 --> 34:52.799
I'm proud of you
for putting yourself out there.

34:53.800 --> 34:58.096
I should never go on another date.
I should just stay away from girls.

34:58.971 --> 35:01.849
Sam, look, you got some stuff
to figure out, but you will.

35:03.643 --> 35:04.894
You're a good guy.

35:04.977 --> 35:07.188
You're sensitive, and you're funny,

35:07.271 --> 35:10.274
and the woman who ends up
with you will be lucky.

35:11.651 --> 35:13.319
You want to marry your best friend.

35:14.654 --> 35:15.530
Edison?

35:15.613 --> 35:16.572
No.

35:17.198 --> 35:18.491
Not your turtle, Sam.

35:18.574 --> 35:20.993
You said my best friend.
He's my best friend.

35:22.078 --> 35:23.121
I just...

35:24.038 --> 35:28.292
I meant you want to be with someone
who appreciates you for what you are.

35:29.127 --> 35:32.797
You know, who loves all
the little odd things about you...

35:33.506 --> 35:34.590
who gets you.

35:37.969 --> 35:39.762
Penguins mate for life, you know?

35:41.389 --> 35:42.515
Yeah?

35:43.850 --> 35:45.184
Well, good for them.

35:46.853 --> 35:50.565
So, how are you feeling now?
Still ready to give up on dating?

35:50.648 --> 35:53.317
I don't know. My dad said to find someone

35:53.401 --> 35:56.571
who appreciates me for what I am,
which is a weirdo.

35:57.530 --> 35:58.614
We talked a lot.

35:58.698 --> 36:00.158
Glad to hear it.

36:00.241 --> 36:03.411
And that makes sense.
You're easy to talk to.

36:07.206 --> 36:08.291
Yeah.

36:09.041 --> 36:10.376
You're easy to talk to, too,

36:10.459 --> 36:13.671
which is good 'cause,
otherwise, you'd go broke.

36:13.754 --> 36:14.964
[chuckles]

36:18.259 --> 36:21.179
[Sam]  When a male gentoo penguin
chooses a mate,

36:21.262 --> 36:22.346
he makes an offering.

36:23.139 --> 36:24.682
He finds a pebble,

36:24.765 --> 36:27.101
often taking the time
to find the smoothest one,

36:27.185 --> 36:29.020
and presents it to the female.

36:29.854 --> 36:32.690
I'm a human,
so it would be weird to offer a pebble.

36:33.357 --> 36:34.233
Julia.

36:36.277 --> 36:39.197
-I've decided I want to give you my brain.
-[gasps] Really?

36:39.280 --> 36:40.448
After I die.

36:41.115 --> 36:42.950
Oh, Sam, that's so great.

36:45.369 --> 36:46.871
You're gonna help so many people.

36:46.954 --> 36:48.581
[chuckles]

36:48.664 --> 36:50.291
Good smile.

36:50.374 --> 36:51.751
It's not creepy at all.

36:51.834 --> 36:53.252
I've been practicing.

36:53.336 --> 36:54.503
Yeah, I can tell.

36:56.839 --> 36:59.425
[Sam]  If the female places the pebble
in her nest,

36:59.508 --> 37:01.219
she accepts him as a mate.

37:01.302 --> 37:03.846
And as you already know,
penguins mate for life.
